title.narrative: OUTPUT 1.4: KNOWLEDGE ON KEY FAMILY PRACTICES

description.narrative: Mothers and other caregivers in targeted localities have improved skills and knowledge on key family practices, which contributes to Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development (Covid), Early Childhood Development, Early Childhood Development (Covid), Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Immunization (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2021, more children under the age of 5 years and women of reproductive age utilize high-impact, quality health and nutrition services.

title.narrative: Mothers and other caregivers in targeted localities have improved skills and knowledge on key family practices

description.narrative: Over 882,500 mothers were more aware of recommended IYCF practices and have enhanced knowledge of key family-based actions including breastfeeding, handwashing at critical times, sleeping under LLINS and home management of diarrhea using ORS. A large number of community platforms, i.e. 3,000 mothers' support groups have strengthened capacities to support the delivery of key messages on health and nutrition interventions across Darfur, Kordofan states, Blue Nile, White Nile, Senna and the East of Sudan (Kassala, Gedaref and Red Sea). | Status:On-track | As-of Date:31/12/2019
